This strategy combines the strength of the SuperTrend indicator with RSI extremes and an optional EMA bias filter to identify high‑probability reversal setups.
• SuperTrend bias: Trades only in the direction of the SuperTrend trend (green = longs, red = shorts).
• RSI trigger: Long entries occur when RSI closes below the oversold threshold, short entries when RSI closes above the overbought threshold. Both levels are fully adjustable.
• EMA filter (optional): You can enable or disable the EMA bias filter. When enabled, longs are only taken above the chosen EMA and shorts only below it. The EMA length is adjustable.
• Risk management: Stop loss is automatically placed at the SuperTrend line, while take profit is set at a fixed pip distance (adjustable).
• Flexibility: All key parameters — ATR period/multiplier, RSI length and thresholds, EMA
